Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.72,0:00:07.06,Default,Ricardo,0000,0000,0000,,Boy?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.67,0:00:09.67,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,This can't be...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.86,0:00:11.56,Default,Ricardo,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.90,0:00:21.81,Default,Felix,0000,0000,0000,,You were spaced out, so I had to pick on you.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.81,0:00:23.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Nyow{\i0} that was a satisfying reaction!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.96,0:00:25.17,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Felis?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.17,0:00:26.74,Default,Felix,0000,0000,0000,,Who else do I look like?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.74,0:00:29.40,Default,Felix,0000,0000,0000,,Did you inhale too much of \Nthe White Whale's fog?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.96,0:00:32.06,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Uh, no... I'm fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.06,0:00:33.87,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,That told me what I wanted to know.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.37,0:00:36.25,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,That means...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.79,0:00:40.88,Default - italics,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,My save point was updated?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.45,0:00:48.16,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,There are a few new things
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.16,0:00:50.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've realized about the Witch's Cult.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.37,0:00:53.77,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Does anyone know of, like...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.77,0:00:57.25,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,a power you can use to overwrite \Nsomeone's consciousness,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.25,0:00:59.87,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,so you psychologically possess them?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.34,0:01:01.28,Default,Julius,0000,0000,0000,,In other words,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.28,0:01:06.27,Default,Julius,0000,0000,0000,,you think the Sin Archbishops \Nmay have such an ability?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.79,0:01:09.73,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, I call it "possession."
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.28,0:01:12.74,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,It's how he stays alive.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.74,0:01:16.11,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,It would explain how he keeps \Npopping up everywhere, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.69,0:01:20.70,Default,Julius,0000,0000,0000,,In an old book, I saw a research \Naccount of a similar subject.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.22,0:01:23.27,Default,Julius,0000,0000,0000,,It's a magic that has been lost,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.27,0:01:26.71,Default,Julius,0000,0000,0000,,but the technique only works \Nunder certain conditions.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.71,0:01:27.41,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Conditions?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.28,0:01:30.11,Default,Julius,0000,0000,0000,,Only members of the Witch's Cult,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.11,0:01:33.50,Default,Julius,0000,0000,0000,,and only a limited number of those,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.50,0:01:34.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,are thought capable of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.29,0:01:37.26,Default,Felix,0000,0000,0000,,And those would be the fingers?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.62,0:01:40.71,Default,Julius,0000,0000,0000,,Most likely, they are the user's spare bodies.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.71,0:01:42.66,Default,Julius,0000,0000,0000,,It's quite a tasteless arrangement.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.66,0:01:45.29,Default,Julius,0000,0000,0000,,I suppose one might call it \Nworthy of a Sin Archbishop.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.86,0:01:47.91,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,So if the Sin Archbishop's confidants,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.91,0:01:50.72,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,the fingers, were wiped out...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.44,0:01:53.05,Default,Julius,0000,0000,0000,,If that happened,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.05,0:01:55.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,his soul would have nowhere to go.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.08,0:01:59.45,Default,Julius,0000,0000,0000,,And that would be the end of him.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.96,0:02:02.92,Default,Julius,0000,0000,0000,,We should first eliminate the \Nfingers in the forest,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.92,0:02:04.88,Default,Julius,0000,0000,0000,,and then face Sloth directly.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.88,0:02:06.31,Default,Julius,0000,0000,0000,,That is my conclusion.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.46,0:02:13.67,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Guys, I need to say one more thing...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.26,0:02:17.42,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry, but I don't think\Nit's only the fingers.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.06,0:02:20.88,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,I think he may be able to possess me, too...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.44,0:02:24.16,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,What do you think I should do?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.91,0:02:25.85,Default,Both,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.68,0:02:28.95,Default - flashback,Bordeaux,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Filthy woman!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.95,0:02:31.81,Default - flashback,Priscilla,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Then, will you also apologize for being born?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.54,0:02:33.01,Default - flashback,Priscilla,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}You silver-haired half-elf.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.81,0:02:35.57,Default - flashback,Priscilla,0000,0000,0000,,Margrave Mathers endorses \Na half-devil? Utter foolishness!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.01,0:02:34.57,Default - flashback,Rickert,0000,0000,0000,,This is a joke!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.01,0:02:37.13,Default - flashback,Priscilla,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Then, will you also apologize for being born?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.17,0:02:38.50,Default - flashback,Emilia,0000,0000,0000,,You know, I had hopes for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.13,0:02:38.08,Default - flashback,Bordeaux,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Filthy woman!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.50,0:02:40.73,Default - flashback,Emilia,0000,0000,0000,,I thought maybe you...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.73,0:02:42.82,Default - flashback,Emilia,0000,0000,0000,,That only you wouldn't give \Nme special treatment.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.82,0:02:44.57,Default - flashback,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,I can't do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.94,0:02:48.79,Default - flashback,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,I can't look at you the way I look at others.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.74,0:02:51.21,Default - flashback,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,It's impossible.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.00,0:02:54.96,Default - flashback,Emilia,0000,0000,0000,,I have no connection to the witch...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.96,0:02:56.42,Default - flashback,Priscilla,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}You silver-haired half-elf.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.35,0:02:56.42,Default - flashback,Bordeaux,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Margrave Mathers endorses a half-devil?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.59,0:03:06.39,Default,Puck,0000,0000,0000,,Lia...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.76,0:03:08.98,Default,Puck,0000,0000,0000,,Your forehead is all wrinkled.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.18,0:03:12.74,Default,Emilia,0000,0000,0000,,Good morning, Puck.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.74,0:03:14.40,Default,Emilia,0000,0000,0000,,You're early today.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.40,0:03:15.65,Default,Puck,0000,0000,0000,,Morning, Lia.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.65,0:03:18.69,Default,Puck,0000,0000,0000,,I thought I'd try going to sleep \Nand waking up earlier.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.41,0:03:21.27,Default,Puck,0000,0000,0000,,That's a lie.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.27,0:03:24.81,Default,Puck,0000,0000,0000,,The truth is that I was worried about you.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.81,0:03:26.82,Default,Puck,0000,0000,0000,,You've had it rough lately.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.82,0:03:28.03,Default,Puck,0000,0000,0000,,Especially yesterday...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.52,0:03:36.68,Default,Emilia,0000,0000,0000,,It was nothing I didn't know already.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.50,0:03:39.21,Default,Puck,0000,0000,0000,,Even if you know you'll fall,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.56,0:03:42.46,Default,Puck,0000,0000,0000,,when it happens, you still hurt and bleed.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.65,0:03:49.06,Default,Emilia,0000,0000,0000,,What do you think I should do, Puck?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.78,0:03:52.45,Default,Emilia,0000,0000,0000,,No, not just me...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.45,0:03:56.83,Default,Emilia,0000,0000,0000,,How can I be better to everyone, \Nand have them be better to me?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.83,0:04:01.90,Default,Puck,0000,0000,0000,,I think you should do what you want.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.48,0:04:06.28,Default,Puck,0000,0000,0000,,I'll be on your side, no matter what you do.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.82,0:04:09.12,Default,Puck,0000,0000,0000,,And no matter what,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.45,0:04:12.20,Default,Puck,0000,0000,0000,,you can't abandon that village, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.71,0:04:16.08,Default,Puck,0000,0000,0000,,Early this morning,\NRam headed out there again.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.28,0:04:18.45,Default,Puck,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe we should wait to hear from her.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.75,0:04:25.55,Default,Puck,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going to check on Betty.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.47,0:04:27.76,Default,Emilia,0000,0000,0000,,Oh... Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.47,0:04:30.47,Default,Emilia,0000,0000,0000,,Tell her hello for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.77,0:04:35.09,Default,Emilia,0000,0000,0000,,Ram?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.09,0:04:38.50,Default,Ram,0000,0000,0000,,Emilia-sama, you have a visitor.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.52,0:04:41.22,Default,Emilia,0000,0000,0000,,You are...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.22,0:04:43.99,Default,Emilia,0000,0000,0000,,from Crusch-sama's household, aren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.43,0:04:47.61,Default,Wilhelm,0000,0000,0000,,I am Wilhelm Trias.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.13,0:04:51.56,Default,Wilhelm,0000,0000,0000,,I have come on my master's behalf.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.56,0:04:53.25,Default,Emilia,0000,0000,0000,,On Crusch-sama's behalf?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.25,0:04:56.57,Default,Emilia,0000,0000,0000,,I received a blank letter\Nfrom her yesterday...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.57,0:04:58.38,Default,Wilhelm,0000,0000,0000,,I see, so it was true.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.41,0:05:01.65,Default,Wilhelm,0000,0000,0000,,While this shames me to say,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.65,0:05:06.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the letter contradicted the message \Nmy master wished to send.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.02,0:05:08.09,Default,Emilia,0000,0000,0000,,Oh... It was a mistake, then?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.51,0:05:11.81,Default,Wilhelm,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, Emilia-sama and Ram-dono...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.69,0:05:14.87,Default,Wilhelm,0000,0000,0000,,We would like to evacuate those remaining
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.87,0:05:17.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,in the mansion, along with the villagers.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.00,0:05:20.15,Default,Wilhelm,0000,0000,0000,,That is Crusch-sama's will.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.15,0:05:20.98,Default,Emilia,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.39,0:05:24.53,Default,Emilia,0000,0000,0000,,There's a ring of criminals near the forest?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.53,0:05:25.31,Default,Ram,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.80,0:05:28.91,Default,Ram,0000,0000,0000,,The punitive force this messenger brought
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.91,0:05:31.64,Default,Ram,0000,0000,0000,,already prepares to fight the enemy.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.64,0:05:36.12,Default,Emilia,0000,0000,0000,,But why would Crusch-sama do \Nso much to help this domain?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.82,0:05:40.65,Default,Wilhelm,0000,0000,0000,,The margrave sent my master a proposal
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.65,0:05:43.25,Default,Wilhelm,0000,0000,0000,,for an alliance with respect \Nto the royal selection.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.77,0:05:47.93,Default,wilhelm,0000,0000,0000,,The condition is a share of the \Nmining rights in Elior Forest.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.35,0:05:49.84,Default,Wilhelm,0000,0000,0000,,Do you understand?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.72,0:05:53.94,Default,Emilia,0000,0000,0000,,So that's what this is about.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.94,0:05:58.31,Default,Wilhelm,0000,0000,0000,,But evacuating all the villagers \Nto the capital will be difficult.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.94,0:06:02.06,Default,Wilhelm,0000,0000,0000,,Half of them will go to the capital.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.06,0:06:05.69,Default,Ram,0000,0000,0000,,I will lead the other half to \Nsafety in the Sanctuary.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.33,0:06:09.30,Default,Ram,0000,0000,0000,,Roswaal-sama is heading there now.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.30,0:06:11.70,Default,Emilia,0000,0000,0000,,O-Oh, I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.70,0:06:14.97,Default,Emilia,0000,0000,0000,,Then, discussion on the\Nmatter is already over.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.68,0:06:19.26,Default,Emilia,0000,0000,0000,,But isn't there something strange about this?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.26,0:06:21.28,Default,Emilia,0000,0000,0000,,It all seems too well-timed—
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.92,0:06:24.04,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Pardon me.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.81,0:06:27.55,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,The group hiding in the forest has \Nbeen observed moving strangely.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.58,0:06:30.78,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,We haven't a moment to waste!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.78,0:06:33.76,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Once they make their move, the entire \Nregion will be a sea of blood!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.24,0:06:35.97,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,What will it be, Captain?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.30,0:06:39.00,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,No, Sword Demon Wilhelm-dono?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.88,0:06:41.34,Default,Wilhelm,0000,0000,0000,,Emilia-sama?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.80,0:06:47.35,Default,Emilia,0000,0000,0000,,I understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.35,0:06:50.02,Default,Emilia,0000,0000,0000,,I gratefully accept your kindness.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.82,0:06:52.95,Default,Emilia,0000,0000,0000,,Has this been explained to the villagers?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.95,0:06:56.52,Default,Ram,0000,0000,0000,,They have been informed in a \Ntimely fashion, Emilia-sama.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.09,0:06:58.14,Default,Emilia,0000,0000,0000,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.71,0:07:00.50,Default,Puck,0000,0000,0000,,Betty says she'll stay here.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.50,0:07:01.37,Default,Emilia,0000,0000,0000,,Puck!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.76,0:07:04.89,Default - flashback,Beatrice,0000,0000,0000,,Betty can't go.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.89,0:07:07.42,Default - flashback,Beatrice,0000,0000,0000,,I'll wait for your return, I suppose.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.42,0:07:09.47,Default - flashback,Beatrice,0000,0000,0000,,You don't have to worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.38,0:07:12.52,Default,Puck,0000,0000,0000,,That's what she said.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.52,0:07:13.85,Default,Puck,0000,0000,0000,,Well, in Betty's case,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.85,0:07:16.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the forbidden library is a much safer place.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.65,0:07:20.81,Default,Puck,0000,0000,0000,,Besides, due to her contract, \Nshe can't leave the mansion.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.81,0:07:22.35,Default,Puck,0000,0000,0000,,Lia, you know that, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.92,0:07:25.96,Default,Emilia,0000,0000,0000,,No fair using that as a reason...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.96,0:07:29.53,Default,Puck,0000,0000,0000,,So, since my cute little sister \Nwill be staying here,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.53,0:07:31.71,Default,Puck,0000,0000,0000,,we shouldn't do anything to the mansion.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.71,0:07:33.95,Default,Puck,0000,0000,0000,,Betty is sweet and kind,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.95,0:07:35.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but she'll show no mercy.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.82,0:07:38.62,Default,Wilhelm,0000,0000,0000,,Understood, Great Spirit.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.58,0:07:45.24,Default,Puck,0000,0000,0000,,You should do what you want.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.24,0:07:48.52,Default,Puck,0000,0000,0000,,I'm on your side, and yours alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.26,0:07:53.50,Default,Emilia,0000,0000,0000,,We will evacuate.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.25,0:07:57.43,Default,Emilia,0000,0000,0000,,I don't want to endanger the villagers!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.72,0:08:08.77,Default,Petra,0000,0000,0000,,We're ready, miss.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.84,0:08:13.94,Default,Emilia,0000,0000,0000,,Um, I think there's been some kind of mistake.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.94,0:08:17.01,Default,Ram,0000,0000,0000,,No, given the number of people and carriages,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.01,0:08:20.41,Default,Ram,0000,0000,0000,,we must ask you to ride with these children.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.01,0:08:22.57,Default,Ram,0000,0000,0000,,It's a necessary measure.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.20,0:08:25.48,Default,Emilia,0000,0000,0000,,Can't we put them in a different carriage?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.48,0:08:27.21,Default,Emilia,0000,0000,0000,,That would be better for the children—
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.21,0:08:30.88,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,You think no one would want to ride with you?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.72,0:08:35.57,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Have you asked the kids how \Nthey feel about that?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.57,0:08:37.51,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Perhaps you just assume
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.51,0:08:41.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,that they hate you and wouldn't \Nwant to be around you?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.38,0:08:43.93,Default,Emilia,0000,0000,0000,,That isn't...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.49,0:08:46.75,Default,Emilia,0000,0000,0000,,I don't need to ask them.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.75,0:08:48.39,Default,Emilia,0000,0000,0000,,I know it's best for everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.39,0:08:50.82,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Six children and one dragon-drawn carriage.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.65,0:08:53.15,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,If we stumble here,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.66,0:08:56.27,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,how will your wish ever come true?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.98,0:08:58.44,Default,Emilia,0000,0000,0000,,A-Are you...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.84,0:09:01.45,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,What do you think, Petra?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.45,0:09:06.00,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Do you refuse to ride in the \Nsame carriage as she does?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.53,0:09:10.19,Default,Petra,0000,0000,0000,,Of course not.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.13,0:09:14.49,Default,Petra,0000,0000,0000,,Aren't you the lady with the potato stamps?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.49,0:09:19.20,Default,Petra,0000,0000,0000,,The one who came with Subaru to \Nwatch our radio calisthenics!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.50,0:09:20.76,Default,Emilia,0000,0000,0000,,Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.12,0:09:23.27,Default,Petra,0000,0000,0000,,We couldn't see your face,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.27,0:09:27.30,Default,Petra,0000,0000,0000,,but we saw you having a good \Ntime talking with Subaru!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.49,0:09:32.08,Default,Petra,0000,0000,0000,,Come and ride with us.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.33,0:09:35.58,Default,Mildo,0000,0000,0000,,And me!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.58,0:09:37.77,Default,Dyne,0000,0000,0000,,I wanna ride with you!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.77,0:09:39.74,Default,Lucas,0000,0000,0000,,Come on, let's go!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.93,0:09:41.86,Default,Kid,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.86,0:09:43.46,Default,Kid,0000,0000,0000,,Come with us!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.46,0:09:46.48,Default,Kid,0000,0000,0000,,And it's gonna be pulled by a dragon!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.48,0:09:48.40,Default,Kid,0000,0000,0000,,That's so cool!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.39,0:09:53.14,Default,Emilia,0000,0000,0000,,Ram, take care of things at the Sanctuary.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.14,0:09:55.15,Default,Emilia,0000,0000,0000,,Be sure to protect the villagers.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.15,0:09:57.63,Default,Ram,0000,0000,0000,,You take care, as well, Emilia-sama.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.46,0:10:01.66,Default,Emilia,0000,0000,0000,,I need to thank you, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.84,0:10:04.61,Default,Emilia,0000,0000,0000,,Where did he go?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.42,0:10:15.88,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Now, I get it...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.88,0:10:18.78,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,We couldn't figure out how \Nyou guys stayed in touch.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.78,0:10:21.51,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Those metia sure are handy, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.81,0:10:26.97,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,You owe a heavy price for \Nthe crime of interrupting
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.97,0:10:28.79,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,my touching reunion with Emilia!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.45,0:10:30.43,Default,Ketty,0000,0000,0000,,You're...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.98,0:10:34.13,Default,Wilhelm,0000,0000,0000,,Too slow.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.74,0:10:42.55,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,In short, we knew you were a spy.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.55,0:10:44.68,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,How we learned is a trade secret.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.68,0:10:47.90,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,So we set a trap for you,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.90,0:10:50.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the contact for the Witch's Cult.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.92,0:10:53.06,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Two hours.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.64,0:10:57.67,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,You gave your buddies a schedule \Nthat was two hours behind.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.67,0:11:00.49,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,We'll use the time to get Emilia \Nand the others away,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.91,0:11:04.20,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,crush the fingers that know our location,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.49,0:11:08.91,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,and make preparations to \Ncrush your Sin Archbishop.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.46,0:11:12.65,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Having your enemy a step ahead, \Nready to destroy you...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.65,0:11:16.30,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,You're about to learn just \Nhow terrifying that is.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.14,0:11:24.64,Default,Emilia,0000,0000,0000,,May the blessing of the spirits be with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.38,0:11:33.62,Default,Wilhelm,0000,0000,0000,,Good luck.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.57,0:11:39.66,Default,Felix,0000,0000,0000,,This is what enabled you to trick \NEmilia-sama and chase her off?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.05,0:11:41.86,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Don't put it that way...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.86,0:11:44.25,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Even if it's accurate, it makes me sound bad!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.25,0:11:47.43,Default,Julius,0000,0000,0000,,That robe was woven with quite an odd spell.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.95,0:11:49.84,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,It was handmade by Roswaal.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.24,0:11:53.55,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Apparently, a spell is woven into \Nit that prevents recognition.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.55,0:11:56.10,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Originally, it was Emilia's...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.19,0:11:59.93,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't steal it, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.93,0:12:01.27,Default,Felix,0000,0000,0000,,Hmm...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.95,0:12:07.44,Default,Felix,0000,0000,0000,,Well, the plan to correct the mistake \Nwith the blank letter worked out!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.69,0:12:17.68,Default - flashback,Ram,0000,0000,0000,,"The letter was a\Nmistake... It was my fault"?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.68,0:12:22.75,Default,Felix,0000,0000,0000,,And you worked so hard to convince \Nthe villagers, Subaru-{\i1}kyun{\i0}...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.11,0:12:25.04,Default - flashback,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Please!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.37,0:12:29.03,Default - flashback,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Emilia's... She's a girl who will \Nbe friends with all of you,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.03,0:12:32.34,Default - flashback,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,so I want you to give her the \Nchance to convince you!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.69,0:12:37.79,Default - flashback,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure everyone has a lot you'd like to say,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.79,0:12:42.40,Default - flashback,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,but please let us protect you long \Nenough that you get that chance!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.57,0:12:50.69,Default - flashback,Head,0000,0000,0000,,Jeez, you really are hopeless, Subaru-sama.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.56,0:12:59.50,Default - flashback,Head,0000,0000,0000,,If you insist on protecting us so much,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.50,0:13:01.09,Default - flashback,Head,0000,0000,0000,,what choice do we have?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.09,0:13:03.41,Default - flashback,Old,0000,0000,0000,,Getting old is just awful.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.41,0:13:06.16,Default - flashback,Old,0000,0000,0000,,I think my tear glands have weakened.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.03,0:13:08.54,Default - flashback,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you all...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.89,0:13:13.39,Default - flashback,Muraosa,0000,0000,0000,,We should be thanking you, Subaru-sama.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.04,0:13:16.87,Default,Felix,0000,0000,0000,,You actually moved me.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.87,0:13:19.28,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Don't bring it back up! It's embarrassing!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.16,0:13:21.73,Default,Felix,0000,0000,0000,,That just leaves...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.38,0:13:24.51,Default,Felix,0000,0000,0000,,Welcome back! How did it go?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.04,0:13:28.17,Default,Ricardo,0000,0000,0000,,We pulled off a surprise attack\Non the ones our location was leaked to.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.17,0:13:30.31,Default,Ricardo,0000,0000,0000,,If I messed up, I'll retire.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.64,0:13:32.52,Default,Ricardo,0000,0000,0000,,The map did a nice job showin' the way.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.52,0:13:37.20,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Then the mark on the map \Nreally was their base!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.20,0:13:41.53,Default,Ricardo,0000,0000,0000,,I dunno if you'd call 'em fastidious or \Nhigh-strung, but it worked against 'em.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.26,0:13:44.24,Default,Ricardo,0000,0000,0000,,And we got what we were after.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.24,0:13:47.50,Default,Ricardo,0000,0000,0000,,This should shut down their \Ncommunications network.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.33,0:13:50.37,Default,Mimi,0000,0000,0000,,Hooray! We killed 'em all!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.37,0:13:53.13,Default,Tivey,0000,0000,0000,,Don't say that. It makes us sound awful.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.13,0:13:55.60,Default,Tivey,0000,0000,0000,,We took a prisoner, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.98,0:13:57.02,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,A prisoner?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.56,0:14:03.89,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,He isn't in the Witch's Cult...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.26,0:14:08.07,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,I wondered why you hadn't \Nshown up. You were caught?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.62,0:14:14.72,Default,Otto,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know who you are, \Nbut thanks for saving me.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.72,0:14:19.81,Default,Otto,0000,0000,0000,,Actually, I'm really in no mood to \Nsay and mean that, damn it!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.56,0:14:26.83,Default,Julius,0000,0000,0000,,Everything is ready.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.17,0:14:29.28,Default,Julius,0000,0000,0000,,Subaru, we can leave at any time.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.46,0:14:32.09,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Let's do this, everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.09,0:14:33.92,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,We'll begin as planned.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.95,0:14:35.94,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Now...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.54,0:14:38.67,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,This time, we'll finish it!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.24,0:14:43.93,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Let us show both Fate and \NSloth what we can do!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.70,0:14:55.04,Default,Betel,0000,0000,0000,,I've been waiting for you, believer in love.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.04,0:14:59.48,Default,Betel,0000,0000,0000,,I am a Sin Archbishop of the Witch's \NCult, representing Sloth...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.48,0:15:03.05,Default,Betel,0000,0000,0000,,Betelgeuse Romanée-Conti!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.89,0:15:08.18,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Pleasure to meet you, great Sin Archbishop.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.18,0:15:12.88,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,If you could find it within you to add my \Nbody and soul to your fingers' ranks,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.88,0:15:17.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,carrying out the Ordeal, there would \Nbe no greater honor.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.79,0:15:24.22,Default,Betel,0000,0000,0000,,How wondrous, how vivacious your faith is!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.91,0:15:27.09,Default,Betel,0000,0000,0000,,To think there was such a devout believer.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.09,0:15:29.37,Default,Betel,0000,0000,0000,,Please forgive my sloth,\Nfor failing to find him.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.37,0:15:34.31,Default,Betel,0000,0000,0000,,Forgive me! Forgive me! Forgive me! \NForgive me! Forgive me!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.31,0:15:36.03,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Please stop, Archbishop.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.03,0:15:39.01,Default,Betel,0000,0000,0000,,Ah... But, but, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.01,0:15:44.85,Default,Betel,0000,0000,0000,,I have no way to atone for my sloth \Nand foolishness but by punishment.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.85,0:15:47.05,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,That's not true.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.05,0:15:50.56,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,The witch wouldn't want to see \Nher beloved believer in pain.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.56,0:15:53.62,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,She would be happier to see \Nyou carry out the Ordeal!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.78,0:15:57.33,Default,Betel,0000,0000,0000,,You are exactly right...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.72,0:15:59.25,Default,Betel,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, the Ordeal.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.25,0:16:02.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What she needs from me now is the Ordeal!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.44,0:16:06.04,Default,Betel,0000,0000,0000,,Your words have opened my eyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.04,0:16:08.29,Default,Betel,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you! Thank you!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.29,0:16:11.79,Default,Betel,0000,0000,0000,,With this Ordeal, we must test her...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.79,0:16:14.59,Default,Betel,0000,0000,0000,,To learn if this half-devil\Nis a worthy vessel,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.59,0:16:17.35,Default,Betel,0000,0000,0000,,if she is worthy to put the witch into.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.48,0:16:21.27,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Put the witch into? Vessel?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.68,0:16:25.13,Default,Betel,0000,0000,0000,,If she is, the witch will possess her. \NIf not, reject her.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.39,0:16:28.45,Default,Betel,0000,0000,0000,,If she proves an unworthy\Nvessel for the witch,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.45,0:16:34.21,Default,Betel,0000,0000,0000,,then the witch will be reborn into this \Nworld on the coming fated day...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.21,0:16:39.91,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,You're saying Emilia is secondary, \Nwithout intrinsic value, to you?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.40,0:16:43.00,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,You monster...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.76,0:16:47.49,Default,Betel,0000,0000,0000,,The words inscribed in the \NGospel tell of her love.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.49,0:16:49.97,Default,Betel,0000,0000,0000,,All of it guides my path!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.46,0:16:52.05,Default,Betel,0000,0000,0000,,Show me your Gospel.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.53,0:16:56.46,Default,Betel,0000,0000,0000,,What is that?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.96,0:17:00.70,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Just what it looks like. A metia, Archbishop.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.65,0:17:03.92,Default,Felix,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, I see him! I see him!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.92,0:17:07.29,Default,Felix,0000,0000,0000,,His face looks just as scary as I'd heard!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.74,0:17:09.45,Default,Betel,0000,0000,0000,,Exactly who are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.45,0:17:12.33,Default,Betel,0000,0000,0000,,No! {\i1}What{\i0} are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.33,0:17:14.75,Default,Felix,0000,0000,0000,,Now, then... Tora, Tora, Tora.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.58,0:17:23.92,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Our surprise attack is a success!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.92,0:17:28.59,Default,Betel,0000,0000,0000,,What? Surprise attack... Surprise attack...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.12,0:17:32.18,Default,Betel,0000,0000,0000,,Then, what do you think of this?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.54,0:17:38.60,Default,Betel,0000,0000,0000,,How? How can you see my Authority?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.25,0:17:40.41,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Who knows?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.41,0:17:44.07,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Ask the witch that left her scent all over me.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.53,0:17:45.59,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, that's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.59,0:17:50.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Unlike me, you haven't received the pass \Nthat lets you meet the witch anytime.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.66,0:17:53.42,Default,Betel,0000,0000,0000,,What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.42,0:17:56.24,Default,Betel,0000,0000,0000,,How dare you speak as though you \Nare intimate with the witch?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.91,0:17:59.82,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,We're so close, she's grabbed my heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.82,0:18:00.75,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Literally...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.20,0:18:03.86,Default,Betel,0000,0000,0000,,I-Inconceivable!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.54,0:18:06.67,Default,Betel,0000,0000,0000,,That cannot be!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.64,0:18:09.51,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go, Patrasche!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.54,0:18:18.39,Default,Betel,0000,0000,0000,,Do not presume you can escape.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.49,0:18:20.68,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Here he comes, here he comes, here he comes!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.68,0:18:22.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's coming, he's coming, he's coming!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.16,0:18:23.98,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Keep it up, Patrasche!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.44,0:18:26.98,Default,Betel,0000,0000,0000,,Futile! Impossible!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.98,0:18:30.67,Default,Betel,0000,0000,0000,,Vanish in the face of my diligence!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.39,0:18:36.44,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry to always rely on you...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.44,0:18:38.54,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,You're the best, Patrasche!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.54,0:18:40.38,Default,Betel,0000,0000,0000,,But... But, but, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.38,0:18:41.87,Default,Betel,0000,0000,0000,,But!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.87,0:18:43.33,Default,Betel,0000,0000,0000,,This is the end, the end!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.68,0:18:51.02,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,You guys...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.02,0:18:53.40,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,You almost caught me in that!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.40,0:18:55.69,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks, though. I thought I was a goner.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.69,0:18:57.72,Default,Mimi,0000,0000,0000,,You're welcome! Yay!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.72,0:19:00.83,Default,Tivey,0000,0000,0000,,Is that man in the sky the Sin Archbishop?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.89,0:19:04.01,Default,Mimi,0000,0000,0000,,Yikes! What the heck is that?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.01,0:19:06.75,Default,Mimi,0000,0000,0000,,There's a man flying, all balled up! Wow!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.75,0:19:09.52,Default,Tivey,0000,0000,0000,,I've never seen anything so creepy in flight.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.52,0:19:12.56,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,That's how it looks to you guys?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.56,0:19:14.70,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Either way, leave him to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.70,0:19:16.70,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Watch the rear, like we planned!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.14,0:19:20.57,Default,Tivey,0000,0000,0000,,Got it! You heard him, Sis!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.57,0:19:22.79,Default,Mimi,0000,0000,0000,,Aye-aye! Hey, Bro.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.79,0:19:24.87,Default,Mimi,0000,0000,0000,,Beat him now, and you'll look awesome!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.13,0:19:27.08,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, I got this!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.74,0:19:29.52,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Bring it on, Archbishop!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.52,0:19:31.04,Default,Betel,0000,0000,0000,,What...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.04,0:19:34.63,Default,Betel,0000,0000,0000,,Just what... What are you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.98,0:19:37.72,Default,Betel,0000,0000,0000,,That cannot be.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.72,0:19:42.81,Default,Betel,0000,0000,0000,,None of this is in the Gospel, \Nin the guide to my destiny!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.81,0:19:46.58,Default,Betel,0000,0000,0000,,What... Just what are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.58,0:19:49.29,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,You've asked that four times.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.29,0:19:51.68,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,If we're talking nightmares, \NI've had far more than you.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.68,0:19:55.53,Default,Betel,0000,0000,0000,,Then... Then, then... You truly are Pride's...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.94,0:19:57.99,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,My name is Natsuki Subaru,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.57,0:20:02.20,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,the silver-haired, half-elf Emilia's knight.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.69,0:20:08.42,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know anything about this "Pride" \Nstuff, but that's the only title I want.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.42,0:20:10.26,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,I don't need any others.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.28,0:20:16.80,Default,Betel,0000,0000,0000,,This place is...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.46,0:20:20.76,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,It's a place where my time once ended.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.26,0:20:25.31,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,And it will be where your time ends, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.98,0:20:30.06,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,That's what this place is.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.06,0:20:33.89,Default,Betel,0000,0000,0000,,If your goal was to lead me out here,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.89,0:20:36.26,Default,Betel,0000,0000,0000,,what have you prepared for me?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.26,0:20:38.95,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,What else? Your natural enemy.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.95,0:20:41.16,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,One you and I have in common...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.35,0:20:45.53,Default,Julius,0000,0000,0000,,"Natural enemy"?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.53,0:20:48.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, that's a fine thing to call me.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.43,0:20:59.16,Default,Julius,0000,0000,0000,,I am Julius Euclius, of the \NLugunica Imperial Knights.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.16,0:21:02.14,Default,Julius,0000,0000,0000,,I am the Kingdom's sword that will slay you.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.37,0:21:05.28,Default,Betel,0000,0000,0000,,A spirit arts user, are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.28,0:21:08.47,Default,Betel,0000,0000,0000,,How truly... How truly...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.60,0:21:11.07,Default,Betel,0000,0000,0000,,Is this also part of your plot?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.07,0:21:14.66,Default,Betel,0000,0000,0000,,I have never known such humiliation!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.66,0:21:17.58,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Really? Well, make the most of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.83,0:21:20.53,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,That's your bill for all you've done.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.36,0:21:24.22,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Let's do it, Julius.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.22,0:21:25.35,Default,Julius,0000,0000,0000,,Are you sure?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.75,0:21:29.55,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,I won't back down, I won't bend, I can't lose.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.55,0:21:31.90,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,I don't want to lose anyone else.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.21,0:21:35.13,Default,Julius,0000,0000,0000,,I am the man who brutally beat you.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.74,0:21:40.41,Default,Julius,0000,0000,0000,,I still believe my behavior was \Nbacked by meaning and reason,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.41,0:21:43.11,Default,Julius,0000,0000,0000,,but that is no more than self-justification,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.11,0:21:45.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,which has nothing to do with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.99,0:21:50.24,Default,Julius,0000,0000,0000,,Can you trust me?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.49,0:21:54.70,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,I hate you.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.70,0:21:57.12,Default,Julius,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, I know.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.12,0:22:00.38,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Having someone break your arms \Nand legs like that is traumatic.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.38,0:22:02.24,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Don't you know the meaning of restraint?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.35,0:22:06.62,Default,Julius,0000,0000,0000,,Just so you know, I did hold back quite a bit.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.05,0:22:09.96,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Seriously? That was you holding back?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.45,0:22:13.33,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,You really are the biggest jerk.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.02,0:22:17.71,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,I really hate you, greatest knight.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.21,0:22:20.29,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,So...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.27,0:22:23.26,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,I will trust you.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.05,0:22:29.04,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,My shame attests to my knowledge \Nthat you are an incredible knight.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:29.04,0:22:32.31,Default,Julius,0000,0000,0000,,Then, with all my soul...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.17,0:22:34.96,Default,Julius,0000,0000,0000,,I shall live up to that!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:35.89,0:22:38.58,Default,Betel,0000,0000,0000,,Is this farce over yet?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:39.01,0:22:43.57,Default,Betel,0000,0000,0000,,What do you expect adding a single \Nspirit arts user to your ranks will do?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.57,0:22:46.92,Default,Betel,0000,0000,0000,,I will defeat you all, tear apart \Nthose who remain,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.92,0:22:49.34,Default,Betel,0000,0000,0000,,resume the Ordeal, and that is all.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.34,0:22:53.25,Default,Betel,0000,0000,0000,,My diligence knows neither slothful \Nresignation nor demise!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.00,0:22:58.49,Default,Betel,0000,0000,0000,,Sloth! Sloth! Sloth!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:58.49,0:23:00.56,Default,Betel,0000,0000,0000,,Sloth!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.18,0:23:02.93,Default - italics,Julius,0000,0000,0000,,Al Clarista!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.83,0:23:16.01,Default,Betel,0000,0000,0000,,You... You should not be able to see it.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.01,0:23:17.76,Default,Betel,0000,0000,0000,,It should be invisible to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.76,0:23:20.83,Default,Betel,0000,0000,0000,,My Unseen Hand can't be seen, can't be seen...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.83,0:23:22.16,Default,Betel,0000,0000,0000,,You can't see it!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.16,0:23:24.97,Default,Betel,0000,0000,0000,,And by two... Two people other than me!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:24.97,0:23:27.66,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,I'm the only one who can see it, Betelgeuse.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.66,0:23:28.45,Default,Betel,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.30,0:23:33.25,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Julius can only see what I'm seeing.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.25,0:23:36.16,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,It also feels much creepier than I expected.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.16,0:23:39.35,Default,Julius,0000,0000,0000,,I can use Nect to consciously\Nshare your senses,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.35,0:23:41.68,Default,Julius,0000,0000,0000,,as well as to maintain them for a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.43,0:23:47.46,Default,Julius,0000,0000,0000,,When you first proposed this, \NI questioned your sanity.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.46,0:23:49.64,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,It worked, didn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:49.64,0:23:51.10,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,A man's all about guts.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:51.10,0:23:52.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You've gotta be open to anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:54.71,0:23:56.63,Default,Betel,0000,0000,0000,,Curse you, curse you...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.63,0:23:59.57,Default,Betel,0000,0000,0000,,Curse you! Curse you! Curse you! Curse you!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:59.57,0:24:03.03,Default,Betel,0000,0000,0000,,Curse you!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:04.26,0:24:07.24,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Sharing a collective body with \Nyou is pretty disgusting.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:07.71,0:24:09.66,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Let's get this over with.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.66,0:24:11.45,Default,Julius,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, let's.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:16.65,0:24:18.84,Default,Julius,0000,0000,0000,,Using your eyes, I shall slay him...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:23.04,0:24:25.73,Default,Julius,0000,0000,0000,,My friend, Natsuki Subaru!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:25.73,0:24:30.00,Episode Title,Title,0000,0000,0000,,The Self-Proclaimed {\c&H84776F&}Knight {\c&HFFFFFF&}and the Greatest {\c&HF7BBC9&}Knight
